==English==

===Adverb===
'''literally'''

# In the direct, [[word for word]] sense. With neither [[idiom]] nor [[metaphor]].
#: ''He's '''literally''' swimming with the fishes.''
# {{colloquial}} A rhetorical device by which the speaker underscores the seriousness of their statement, even though the statement is not true in a word for word sense.
#: ''I '''literally''' felt like I wanted to vomit when I saw that ugly dress.''

